@0x004a 

> When typing a line wider than terminal width, it skips a line. (not sure why)

It's a known issue in the terminal stdlib we're using unfortunately, related info here: https://github.com/shazow/ssh-chat/issues/22

Do you think we could get away with just doing something like this instead?

``` go
// in sshd/terminal.go:NewTerminal
...
go func() {
    for range time.Tick(keepaliveInterval) {
        _, err := channel.SendRequest("keepalive", true, nil)
        if err != nil {
            // We'll get an err when the channel is closed, so this goroutine
            // will clean up itself. Bonus points for catching a specific err.
            return
        }
    }
}()
```

Might be a bit nicer since we avoid introducing more parameters/state to unrelated functions.

